events.name: Auburn Tigers at LSU Tigers

headlines.description: Rueben Randle caught a 42-yard scoring pass from Jordan Jefferson and a 46-yard touchdown pass from Jarrett Lee, and No. 1 LSU once again overcame off-the-field distractions in style with a 45-10 victory over 19th-ranked Auburn on Saturday.

events.name: Tennessee Volunteers at Alabama Crimson Tide

headlines.description: AJ McCarron passed for 284 yards and a touchdown and ran for another score to lead No. 2 Alabama to a second-half surge and a 37-6 rout of Tennessee Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Alabama breaks tie, pounds Vols in second half

events.name: Texas Tech Red Raiders at Oklahoma Sooners

headlines.description: Seth Doege threw for 441 yards and connected with Alex Torres on three of his four touchdown passes, and Texas Tech snapped No. 3 Oklahoma's 39-game home winning streak with 41-38 victory Saturday night.

events.name: Oklahoma State Cowboys at Missouri Tigers

headlines.description: Joseph Randle scored four touchdowns, two on runs that capitalized on big defensive plays by Shaun Lewis, as No. 6 Oklahoma State remained unbeaten and ended Missouri's 10-game home winning streak with a 45-24 victory on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Okla. St. rolls without top WRs

events.name: Air Force Falcons at Boise State Broncos

headlines.description: Kellen Moore threw three touchdowns, Doug Martin scored twice and the defense and special teams did just enough to help No. 5 Boise State hold off Air Force in a 33-26 victory Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Boise State holds off challenge from Air Force

events.name: Wisconsin Badgers at Michigan State Spartans

headlines.description: Keith Nichol caught a 44-yard Hail Mary on the game's final play for a tiebreaking touchdown, giving Michigan State (No. 16 BCS, No. 15 AP) a stunning 37-31 win over No. 4 Wisconsin (No. 6, No. 4) on Saturday night.

events.name: North Carolina Tar Heels at Clemson Tigers

headlines.description: Tajh Boyd tied a school record with five touchdown passes, defensive end Kourtnei Brown scored on interception and fumble returns and No. 8 Clemson improved to 8-0 for the first time in 11 years with a 59-38 victory over North Carolina on Saturday.

events.name: Washington Huskies at Stanford Cardinal

headlines.shortLinkText: Stanford runs for 446 yards, routs Washington

events.name: Arkansas Razorbacks at Ole Miss Rebels

headlines.description: Tyler Wilson threw for 232 yards and rushed for two touchdowns and No. 10 Arkansas rallied from an early 17-point deficit to beat Mississippi 29-24 on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Arkansas rallies from 17 down, nips Ole Miss

events.name: Oregon Ducks at Colorado Buffaloes

headlines.description: Playing without Darron Thomas and LaMichael James, No. 9 Oregon bulldozed injury-riddled Colorado 45-2 Saturday.

events.name: Kansas State Wildcats at Kansas Jayhawks

headlines.description: Collin Klein threw for a career-high 195 yards and accounted for five touchdowns, freshman Tyler Lockett returned a kickoff for a score and caught a touchdown pass, and No. 12 Kansas State pasted Kansas 59-21 on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: K-State still unbeaten after smashing Kansas

events.name: Boston College Eagles at Virginia Tech Hokies

headlines.description: David Wilson got Virginia Tech's offense untracked with a touchdown run in the third quarter and Logan Thomas threw for a TD and ran for another as the Hokies (No. 12 BCS, No. 16 AP) beat Boston College 30-14 Saturday for their third straight win.
headlines.shortLinkText: Virginia Tech tops BC for 3rd straight victory

events.name: Nebraska Cornhuskers at Minnesota Golden Gophers
Texas A&M Aggies at Iowa State Cyclones

headlines.description: Ryan Tannehill threw for 263 yards and two touchdowns and 17th-ranked Texas A&M held off Iowa State 33-17 on Saturday for its third straight Big 12 win.
headlines.shortLinkText: Two rush for over 100 as A&M tops Iowa St.

events.name: Marshall Thundering Herd at Houston Cougars

headlines.description: Case Keenum became the Football Bowl Subdivision's career leader in total offense on Saturday, throwing for 376 yards and tying his career high with six touchdown passes in Houston's 63-28 win over Marshall.
headlines.shortLinkText: Keenum sets NCAA record as Houston cruises

events.name: Penn State Nittany Lions at Northwestern Wildcats

headlines.description: Joe Paterno tied Eddie Robinson's Division I record with his 408th career victory Saturday night as Penn State beat Northwestern 34-24.
headlines.shortLinkText: Paterno equals Robinson's Div. I wins record

events.name: Georgia Tech Yellow Jackets at Miami Hurricanes

headlines.description: JoJo Nicholas recovered a fumbled punt for a touchdown plus added an interception, Lamar Miller ran for 93 yards and a score and Miami's banged-up defense was dominant as the Hurricanes topped No. 20 Georgia Tech 24-7 on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Miami romps to hand Ga. Tech 2nd straight loss

events.name: Illinois Fighting Illini at Purdue Boilermakers

headlines.description: Caleb TerBush passed for 178 yards and two touchdowns to help Purdue upset No. 23 Illinois 21-14 on Saturday afternoon.
headlines.shortLinkText: Purdue hands No. 23 Illinois 2nd straight loss

events.name: Cincinnati Bearcats at South Florida Bulls

headlines.description: Zach Collaros threw for three touchdowns and ran for two fourth-quarter scores, helping Cincinnati come from behind in the closing minutes to stay atop the Big East standings with a 37-34 victory over South Florida.
headlines.shortLinkText: Collaros' TD drives Cincy by USF in final minute

events.name: Jacksonville State Gamecocks at Kentucky Wildcats

headlines.description: CoShik Williams ran for a career-high 148 yards and Kentucky snapped a four-game losing streak with a 38-14 win over Jacksonville State on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Williams rushes for 148 as Kentucky snaps skid

events.name: Northern Illinois Huskies at Buffalo Bulls
Indiana Hoosiers at Iowa Hawkeyes

headlines.description: Marvin McNutt caught three touchdown passes to become Iowa's career leader and Marcus Coker ran for two more scores to lead the Hawkeyes past Indiana 45-24 on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: McNutt breaks Iowa receiving TDs record in win

events.name: Wake Forest Demon Deacons at Duke Blue Devils

headlines.description: Tanner Price's 64-yard touchdown pass to Chris Givens with 6:52 left lifted Wake Forest to its 12th straight victory over Duke, 24-23 on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Wake Forest tallies 12th straight win over Duke

Louisiana Tech Bulldogs at Utah State Aggies
South Alabama Jaguars at Georgia State Panthers
Maryland Terrapins at Florida State Seminoles

headlines.description: EJ Manuel passed for 264 yards and a touchdown, and freshman Devonta Freeman ran for 100 yards a second straight week as Florida State routed Maryland 41-16 on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Led by Manuel, Florida State pummels Maryland

events.name: New Hampshire Wildcats at UMass Minutemen
Temple Owls at Bowling Green Falcons
Old Dominion Monarchs at Villanova Wildcats
NC State Wolfpack at Virginia Cavaliers

headlines.description: Mike Glennon threw for three touchdowns and David Amerson intercepted two passes as North Carolina State defeated Virginia 28-14 on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Glennon tosses 3 TDs, NC State edges Virginia

events.name: Ohio Bobcats at Akron Zips
Samford Bulldogs at Appalachian State Mountaineers
East Carolina Pirates at Navy Midshipmen

headlines.description: Dominique Davis set two NCAA records for consecutive completions, connecting on all 26 of his first-half throws to extend his streak to 36 straight over two games, and East Carolina squeezed past skidding Navy 38-35 on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: ECU's Davis completes 26 straight throws in win

events.name: Memphis Tigers at Tulane Green Wave
Louisiana Ragin' Cajuns at Western Kentucky Hilltoppers
Fresno State Bulldogs at Nevada Wolf Pack
Louisiana Monroe Warhawks at North Texas Mean Green
Utah Utes at California Golden Bears

headlines.description: Zach Maynard threw for one touchdown and ran for another and California's defense completely shut down Utah's offense to help the Golden Bears get their first Pac-12 win of the season, 34-10 over the Utes on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Maynard's arm, legs power Cal romp over Utah

events.name: Army Black Knights at Vanderbilt Commodores

headlines.description: Zac Stacy set career highs with 198 yards rushing and three touchdowns, Jordan Rodgers made a promising debut at quarterback and Vanderbilt beat Army 44-21 on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Stacy burns Army for 198, 3 TDs as Vandy rolls

Gardner-Webb Bulldogs at Coastal Carolina Chanticleers

headlines.shortLinkText: Barkley throws for 3 TDs as USC drops Notre Dame

headlines.shortLinkText: Mannion's 4 TDs power Oregon State by Wazzu
